.TH cerebrod.conf 5 "May 2005" "cerebrod.conf @VERSION@" "cerebrod.conf"
.SH "NAME"
cerebrod.conf \- cerebrod configuration file
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The 
.B cerebrod
configuration file configures the features and behavior of the
.B cerebrod
daemon.  The configuration ultimately affects the utility of
the
.B Cerebro
suite of tools and libraries.

The default configuration file loaded by
.B cerebrod
is @CEREBROD_CONFIGFILE_DEFAULT@, however an alternate configuration
file can be specified on the command line with the
.I -c
option.

.SH "CONFIGURATION OPTIONS"
The following are a list of configuration options that can be
specified in the configuration file.  Each configuration option must
be listed on a separate line.  Arguments for an option are separated
by any amount of whitespace.  Multiple arguments are also separated by
whitespace.  Comments can be marked by using the pound sign ("#")
character, and lines can be continued on the next using backslash
("\\").
